message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in New Zealand, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling is another convenient option. New Zealand has well-maintained cycling paths in many areas, making it safe and enjoyable to ride to your destination.

3. Public Transportation: Check if there are any bus routes that pass by or near the grocery store. You can use public transportation to reach your destination. Look up the local bus schedules and plan your trip accordingly.

4. Carpooling or Taxi: If you have a friend or neighbor who is heading to the grocery store, you can ask for a ride and carpool together. Alternatively, you can use a taxi or ridesharing service to reach the store quickly.

Consider the weather conditions, your personal preferences, and the availability of transportation options to choose the most suitable method for your trip to the grocery store.
